result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:15 AM Cases called: 21CF657 and 22CF174. Prosecuting attorney Peggy A. Crooks-Mishacoff in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Justin Aaron Warren in court.  Attorney Richard G. Davis Jr. in court for Justin Aaron Warren. Agreement recited by State. Court reviewed the rights & elements. Defendant pled no contest to counts 1 & 2 of 21CF657. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment. Count 3 dismissed and read in. 22CF174 dismissed and read in. Sentencing statements. Court withheld sentence, placed the defendant on probation for 24 months. Conditions of probation include: Maintain absolute sobriety. Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations. Submit DNA sample. Comply with any treatment agent recommends. No contact with JPE, or his residence, SJE, ARAE, and BTE, unless agent changes. Costs on count 1 of $443.00 and count 2 $243.00. and 30 days jail, with Huber (count 2). Jail start 8/26/22 at 7:00 PM 3 days credit. 10:37 AM
